X Carbon is a smart drone that flies in the air and helps reduce pollution.
It takes in polluted air using fans, then uses high voltage electricity to break carbon dioxide (CO₂) into carbon and oxygen. The oxygen is released back into the air, making it cleaner, and the carbon is collected and reused to make useful products like ink.

The drone is intelligent—it can move on its own using a camera (ESP32-CAM), detect polluted areas, and decide where to go. There is also a second version that can be attached to cars to reduce pollution directly from vehicles.

A mobile app is connected to the system, which shows pollution levels, drone location, and performance in real time.
